developerNotes:
I have modified the report so that the Department column heading uses the first row of the ReportInformation Department Column (This is similar to the column TIN expression). The department is derived from the r_Department column in the ReportTextsPivot. Any client that wants to change the default of the column heading will need update the ReportText r_Department and run the spf_RebuildReportTextsPivot to update i.e. 
EXEC spt_ConfigureReportText
    @ReportTextCode = 'r_Department',
    @ReportText = 'Segmentation',
    @LanguageCode = 'English';

EXEC spf_RebuildReportTextsPivot
GO

Implemented the logic to allow setting the max file size per Tax Return Design.

e.g. to set Individual - VAT to 20Mb run:

EXEC spt_ConfigureDocumentation
    @DocumentationTypeCode       = 'TaxReturn',
    @DocumentTypeCode            = 'SupportingDocument',
    @DocumentTypeDescription     = 'Supporting Document',
    @IsRequired                  = 0,
    @MaxFileSize                 = 20480,
    @TaxReturnDesignTypeCode     = 'STD',
    @TaxTypeCode                 = 'VAT',
    @TaxReturnDesignCommenceDate = '20140101';
